{"className":"RichTextParagraphNode","align":"left","children":[
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"Pietra Index is defined as twice the maximal area of a triangle that can be fitted between the ROC curve of the model and the diagonal of the unit square. The multiplication by 2 ensures that the range of possible values for the index is [0,1]. The closer the Pietra index is to unity, the better the rating model."}]},
{"className":"RichTextParagraphNode","align":"left","children":[
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"Pietra index is calculated under the assumption that the area under the ROC is convex. In this case the Pietra Index matches the Kolmogorov-Smirnov statistic indicated by the vertical dotted line in the plot."}]},
